      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_301751_1816_04_03_page01.jpg"/>
            <!--filenames for photos associated with this letter. Example: <pb n="1" facs="image1.jpg image2.jpg image3.jpg"/> -->
            <opener>
               <dateline><!--If there's no date line, omit this element. Record in the order in which it is written on the letter.-->
                  <name type="place" ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/>Edgeworth's Town
                  <date when="1816-04-03"/>April 3[superscript]d[/superscript]. 1816. </dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BerrA1"><persName  ref="./Personography.xml#BerrM1">Miss Berrys</persName></persName>;
                     <!-- Use if letter has a saluation ("Dear Sir," for example). If not, delete this line.-->
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>The very polite and kind<lb/>
               attention you did me the<lb/>
               honor to pay to a former<lb/>
               note of introduction <choice><orig>en-<lb/>
                  -courages</orig><reg>encourages</reg></choice>me, you see to<lb/>
               encroach upon your<lb/>
               goodness and to venture<lb/>
               to present to you another<lb/>
               of my brothers -<persName>my eldest <lb/>
                  brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL2">Lovell Edgeworth</persName></persName><lb/>
               - who has had so large a<lb/>
               share of the evils of life<lb/>
               that I cannot help <choice><orig>wish<lb/>
                  -ing</orig><reg>wishing</reg></choice> he should now <choice><orig>en-<lb/>
                     joy</orig><reg>enjoy</reg></choice> as much as possible<lb/>
               of its blessings - and of<lb/>
               one of its best blessings<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_301751_1816_04_03_page02.jpg"/>
               good society - He has<lb/>
               been twelve years a <choice><orig>prison<lb/>
                  -er</orig><reg>prisoner</reg></choice> in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#FR">France</placeName>- detained<lb/>
               by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BonaN1">Bonaparte</persName> from the<lb/>
               time of the breaking out<lb/>
               of the war till the allies<lb/>
               entered <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName> - So that<lb/>
               he is a stranger almost<lb/>
               in his own country &amp;<lb/>
               till the present moment<lb/>
               ill health has prevented<lb/>
               him from fully <choice><orig>enjoy-<lb/>
                  -ing</orig><reg>enjoying</reg></choice> the contrast of the<lb/>
               society in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName> &amp; that<lb/>
               to which he was <choice><orig>condemn-<lb/>
                  -ed</orig><reg>condemned</reg></choice> in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#FR">France</placeName> - May<lb/>
               I hope that you will<lb/>
               do him the honor &amp;<lb/>
               the favor to let him<lb/>
               spend one evening in<lb/>
               the delightful society at<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_301751_1816_04_03_page03.jpg"/>
               your house? -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><persName>My brother <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd E.</persName></persName><lb/>
               begs me to present his<lb/>
               grateful respects to you<lb/>
               - He much regrets that<lb/>
               a note &amp; an invitation<lb/>
               to dinner you did him<lb/>
               the honor to send him<lb/>
               did not reach him<lb/>
               while he was in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName><lb/>
               - It was forwarded<lb/>
               to him to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> by<lb/>
               the post - He was as fully<lb/>
               sensible as I am of your<lb/>
               goodness.<lb/>
               </p>
            <p>We are all at this time<lb/>
               happily engaged in<lb/>
               reading a most <choice><orig>enter-<lb/>
                  taining</orig><reg>entertaining</reg></choice> book in the first<lb/>
               page of which is written<lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">from A &amp; M. Berry</hi>
               It was a present from<lb/>
               the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BerrA1"><persName  ref="./Personography.xml#BerrM1">Miss Berrys</persName></persName> to the<lb/>
               <!--More body paragraphs as needed.-->
               <!--Where there's a page break record it inside the relevant body paragraph like this, 
                  with the self-closing page-break element. n="2" indicates the START of the second page.-->
               <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_301751_1816_04_03_page04.jpg"/>
            </p>
            <p>late <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MaloE1">Mr. Malone</persName> &amp; with<lb/>
               all his valuable library<lb/>
               has come into the <choice><orig>posses-<lb/>
               -sion</orig><reg>possession</reg></choice> of his brother  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SundR1">Lord <lb/>
                  Sunderlin</persName> who is our<lb/>
               neighbor in this country<lb/>
               - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SundR1">His Lordship</persName> has had<lb/>
               the generosity - and I<lb/>
               think it is great generosity<lb/>
               - to trust this precious<lb/>
               book to us - It is <choice><orig>interleav<lb/>
                  -ed</orig><reg>interleaved</reg></choice> &amp; furnished with<lb/>
               prints of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MaloE1">Mr. Malones</persName><lb/>
               collecting of all the persons<lb/>
               mentioned in "the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Remin1"><choice><orig>Remi<lb/>
               niscences</orig><reg>Reminiscences</reg></choice></title>" - What a <choice><orig>de-<lb/>
               lightful</orig><reg>delightful</reg></choice> companion <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WalpH1">Lord<lb/>
                  Orford</persName> must have been &amp;<lb/>
               how <hi rend="underline">much</hi> we are obliged<lb/>
               to those who have <choice><orig>preserv-<lb/>
                  ed</orig><reg>preserved</reg></choice> in its full animation<lb/>
               &amp; elegance the living <choice><orig>spi-<lb/>
                  rit</orig><reg>spirit</reg></choice> of his conversation -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">My father</persName> &amp; <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">Mrs. Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
               beg to present their grateful<lb/>
               respects - Believe me<lb/></p>
            <closer><persName>my dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BerrA1"><persName ref="./Personography.xml#BerrM1">Miss Berrys</persName></persName></persName> Yr. obliged<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
               <!--include linebreaks, if used. example: <closer> Yours<lb/> Very sincerely<lb/> -->
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p><!--A postscript goes here, outside the <closer>. --></p>
            </postscript>
            <!--You can include a <pb/> here, or inside the postScript.-->
            <!-- Format for postscripts. 
               Postscripts do NOT go inside closer tags. Adjust to take into account the order in your letter. 
               Sometimes the signature is on page three, the address on page four, then the postscript follows back on the top of page one, for example.-->
